items.description:
FaeTality

Please read the description below for model information!

This is the second model mix that I have publicly released. Originally started as a version upgrade for FaeTastic...I fell in love with it and decided that it needed its own unique name and space.

Like FaeTastic this is a very versatile model that does have the Noise Offset included. I still love FaeTastic and I use it regularly in my work still, but FaeTality I find it to be a bit more creative and also makes some amazing eye details.

I use the F8Anime2 VAE for this model, but the 840k also works perfectly well too. If your colors are appearing washed out, then you need to install and use the VAE properly.

Almost all images utilized Loopback Scaler.

I very highly recommend this script as it does some awesome stuff (why the images example images are highly detailed with awesome vibrant coloring!!). For any images not utilizing it, I instead used the SD Upscale. I've written a guide here going over it for those not versed in upscaling: https://ko-fi.com/post/The-Double-Headed-Issue-E1E0JO2UV

When I have time I plan on publishing some article guides on Civit going over the Loopback Scaler and how to utilize it properly.

This model mix has been a several month long process in the making as I am highly picky about the quality of things that I want to release. That's why I don't churn out things on here (I have A LOT of models and TIs/LORAs but am very anxious about releasing them unless I feel like they've attained high standards!). It probably took hundreds of merges and a crapton of playing with merge sliders to figure out things. If you feel like supporting me here is my Kofi.

Any questions related to the model or any help needed with Civitai I am always available to be contacted via Civitai discord. I don't bite. :)

items.name: Magical Girl Lyrical Nanoha: Official Art Ver.
items.description:
This LoRA is based on official art for the Magical Girl Lyrical Nanoha franchise. I have focused exclusively on the young protagonist, Nanoha, and carefully constructed a training dataset consisting of high quality art and tagging. Over the span of several weeks, I trained and retrained to accurately diffuse a style similar to the official art style. The diffused images should be immediately recognizable for any other collectors of the official Nanoha artworks!

Tagging

The activation tag is 'takamachi nanoha'. If you want her most recognized appearance, add 'twintails' and 'white ribbon'. This is the way she is most often depicted. But the training dataset consists of other hair ornaments and hair styles, so feel free to experiment here. For example, try 'straight hair' for her nighttime hair or 'black ribbon' for Fate's ribbons!

Strength

The strength of the LoRA should be anywhere between 0.6 and 0.8. If you prefer the visual style to match the official art as much as possible, stick with 0.8. The trade-off for this is losing some prompting flexibility. Lower the LoRA strength to regain that flexibility! Anything below 0.6 loses her appearance and the official art style.

Quality

Preview images here on civitai are heavily compressed and introduce quite a few JPG compression artifacts. To see the true quality this LoRA can accomplish, generate one of the preview examples locally and upscale with R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B. Or, click here: https://i.imgur.com/SBQoruy.png.

Feedback

I would love to hear your thoughts and see your diffusions! Please share them~

items.name: Nami - League of Legends
items.description:
Here be my first LoRa, being Nami from League of Legends.

It definitely has some flaws that can be addressed in future versions, but overall it came out pretty well.

Recommended strength ranges from: 0.8 - 1.0

Currently the trigger word is simply 'nami' but will likely change in the future.

Helpful tags include: mermaid, monster girl, blonde hair, colored sclera, black sclera, red eyes, orange eyes, helmet, jewelry

Other tags that were trained in but results will vary: center opening, staff, holding staff

The biggest flaws with the Lora currently are:

  • Hands can easily become fused with fins, so I recommend using tags to encourage emphasizing hands

  • The tail can end up awkwardly short

  • Getting the Lora to properly fill out Nami's 'chest frills' completely is like a 50/50 shot, even with the 'center opening' tag

  • Her staff probably won't look accurate if you try to include

  • It's possible to prompt to remove her helmet but the Lora's very stubborn about it currently (Using tags like "forehead" or "bangs pinned back" will help)

  • I have no idea how to tag her waist armor, so it'll show up and and disappear at its own leisure :(

I intend to update this once I've made improvements (and can get more pictures to use for training)

V1.0是不良人第五季后姬如雪建模的LoRA模型，采用国风3（guofeng3_v32.ckpt [0bb33c7041]
）模型做为底模，基于秋叶的lora整合包进行训练，权重在0.8左右效果比较稳定，配合EasyNegative等负面提示词模型效果更好。这个模型有两种发型，可以通过long hair, ponytail或short hair两组tag来控制长短发。（如果带剑的话，剑的位置不太好控制，容易出现在很奇怪的位置或变成奇怪的样子）

V2.0是不良人第四季姬如雪建模的LoRA模型，采用国风3（guofeng3_v32.ckpt [0bb33c7041]
）模型做为底模，基于秋叶的lora整合包进行训练，权重在0.8左右效果比较稳定，配合EasyNegative等负面提示词模型效果更好。这个模型有两套服饰，两种发型，可以通过blue colothes或miao两组tag来切换两套服装，加headware可以画出苗族头饰。（剑和1.0一样依然不好控制，有的时候背后还会背上龙泉剑，因为素材中有，但是细节还原度不高）

权重在0.8时，面部还原度较高，但是场景、姿势比较固定，v2.0由于训练数据夜景和室内比较多，因此光线有些暗，可以适当降低模型权重或者增加白天等光线tag权重。权重在0.4时，能保留模型主体特征，并提供更大的自由度以更换姿势、服装及背景，画出更通用但不那么还原的图。

初始分辨率540x960，采用R-ESRGAN 4x+放大算法，重绘幅度0.3放大2倍进行高清修复，然后图生图用SD upscale脚本，选择同样的算法，重绘幅度0.1进行超分放大，可以得到效果不错的4k高清图片。（此方法第一步直接生成1080P的图片，比较看脸，不易批量操作，16G显存最多只能同时生成4张图片，出图及修图效率较低，但是质量较高）

items.name: game card's back-(hearthstone)炉石卡背-LoRA V1.0
items.description:
我曾想办法控制中间炉石icon的生成，但由于大部分训练素材来自于炉石，这个控制并不稳定，尤其是某些特定的主体，比如“heaven（天堂）”此类数据除了炉石之外，并没有找到太出色的，但炉石的相关数据又比较多，所以当你输入“heaven”时这个icon就很难去掉。

一下是我的关键词结构，仅供参考：

lora触发词+视觉主题+边框材质+底版材质+中心材质+其他描述+是否要炉石的icon？

就像这样↓

hearthstone_card, steampunk, metal border, metal plate, red-hot metal core, missile, armor, hearthstone's icon in the middle

我的目标是：

使用“game_card”生成没有炉石icon的卡牌；

使用“hearthstone_card”+"hearthstone's icon in the middle"生成带有炉石icon的卡牌；

但结果并不理想，未来的优化方向是，调整tag，丰富数据库，尤其是炉石之外的数据。

另外还有一个尴尬的问题，大部分炉石卡背中间都是一个太阳形状或星形，说以……

但这一点如果prompt描写的足够丰富，就可以避免，如果是简单几个单词，中间很大概率会出现一个类似太阳的形状。

虽然是基于DreamShaper训练但是对ReV Animated和A-Zovya RPG Artist Tools。都有不错的支持。

Translated by GPT↓↓↓-------------------------------

I have tried to control the generation of the Hearthstone icon in the middle, but since most of the training materials come from Hearthstone, the control is not stable, especially for certain specific subjects, such as "heaven." There are not many outstanding data available outside of Hearthstone for this type of data, so it is difficult to remove the icon when you enter "heaven."

Here is my keyword structure for reference:

Lora trigger words + visual theme + border material + bottom plate material + center material + other descriptions + whether to include Hearthstone's icon.

For example:

Hearthstone_card, steampunk, metal border, metal plate, red-hot metal core, missile, armor, Hearthstone's icon in the middle.

My goal is to generate cards without the Hearthstone icon by "game_card" .

Generate cards with the Hearthstone icon by "hearthstone_card" plus "hearthstone's icon in the middle."

However, the results are not ideal, because most of the training materials come from Hearthstone, so it is difficult to control the generation of the Hearthstone icon.

In the future, the optimization direction is to adjust the tags and enrich the database, especially with data outside of Hearthstone. In addition, there is an embarrassing problem: most of the Hearthstone card backs have a sun or star shape in the middle. However, this can be avoided if the prompt description is rich enough. If only a few simple words are used, there is a high probability that a sun-like shape will appear in the middle.

Although I trained based on DreamShaper, ReV Animated and A-Zovya RPG Artist Tools also provide good support.

items.name: XenoEngine - Across the 5th Dimension
items.description:
This merge likes simple (but creative) prompts to create art with the creative versatility of the original XenoEngine 4.5 with a huge push toward semi-realism and fantasy. Though made with portraiture and consistency in mind, it does a nice job as a flexible base model for just about anything I've tried to make with it.

Certain prompts tend to go more "art" than "photography" style. Using "Real Life" along with traditional "photography" cues in the prompt can help bring more semi-realism.

The sample images I have made are done with simple prompts and Easy Negative and Bad Prompts Version 2 - no postwork or cleanup. As always - to get really great stuff with SD, inpainting and cleanup is likely needed.

modelVersions.name: 5th.1
modelVersions.description:
Time for 5th Dimension to get it's tech update. When I applied much of the new learning to my 4.x Art Style XenoEngine, it didn't change the nature of the model all that much. (Most of the experimentation and work I'm doing are geared toward perfecting that model for my game system). When applying it here - the "style" appears mostly the same in terms of portraiture and so on - but the overall composition is quite different.

I've also started a bit of a new approach to things on the learning end. The big thing there is that I'm no longer worried about whether or not the model can do "porn things." We obviously want "sexy" - since this model is primarily for portraits and people - but SD is still a good ways away from being able to spit out complicated things (you know, like sex) without arms and legs going all akimbo.

I am NOT making any special effort to make it NOT do porn - but over the next few generations of these model series we'll be looking at sexy, nude, and all that - but we're not going to be pushing to try to make it good at anything above that MPAA R Rating.

Pepper Hart stands at 5 feet 8 inches (172 cm) tall and weighs 118 lbs (54 kg) with a slim build. She has reddish-brown hair and hazel eyes. Her body measurements are originally 32C-25-35, and she wears a dress size of 38 (EU) and shoe size 8. In 2018, Pepper had her breasts enhanced to size 34F.

Aside from her career in the adult entertainment industry, Pepper is known to be a traveling enthusiast, a dog lover, and an avid selfie taker. Pepper retired from the industry in 2021 after five years of working in the business, but she has left a significant mark on the industry during her time as an actress and model. I won’t always be young and I don’t want to ignore my work while I’m in it." This shows her dedication and passion for her work. Overall, Pepper Hart has made a name for herself in the industry, and her performances in various videos and web scenes have garnered her a large following of fans.

💡Workflow Advice💡

🔧Prompt and Sampling🔧

  • What's the + for?

    • Just an easy way to indicate the dataset image for this particular LORA was based off a minimum of 1024px+ quality source images with the LORA trained at 1024,1024 (I may go higher in the future if I can get a properly working configuration).

    • For the most part, you can start with higher base resolutions to capture more details and/or generate higher quality outputs. See some of the gallery examples.

    • You don't have to gen at high resolution, low res generations will be better quality as well.

  • Most images have been generated with LORA weighted @ .75 - 1.

  • For photoreal shots, I've found sampling steps best well above 50 give better results.

  • ControlNet is your friend. Embrace the dark side.😈

    • Tile pre-sample and model is good for extreme close ups

    • I use segmentation for lots of my generations now.

🗒️Side Notes🗒️

  • This MoC+ series is something new and some LoRAs take a significant amount of time to gather the right dataset. Let me know if I should take the extra time it takes to create these type of LoRAs or just stick with the regular quality.

Since purchasing a few Afremov paintings about 10 years ago, the studio has emailed me thousands of paintings, almost daily. I decided to make a LoRA out of a selection of these.

The Entropy Lora combines organic and inorganic natural surfaces to create a realistic render with an interesting structure. The dataset is based on photography sets from my field trips. The Lora is intended to use as a texture creation helper, for tileable textures, but it also works well in scenes to texture objects. It adds randomness, details, and structure to various photos. To generate only structured textures, you can use higher weights. CLIP SKIP 1-2.
